
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Avoid_Food_Waste";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<div class="container">
    <!--Avoid food waste heading-->
    <h2 class="page-heading">Avoid Food Waste</h2>
    <!--Avoid food waste heading-->
    <p class="text-bold">Click on the below tiles to find out different ways to avoid food waste.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <!--Shop smart category block-->
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="avoid-waste-block">
                <div class="food-tip-img" id="shop-smart">
                    <img src="~/images/shop_smart.png" />
                </div>
                <div id="shop-content-block" class="content-block">
                    <p>Try to avoid going grocery shopping when you are hungry. This might result in buying more products than you actually need.</p>
                    <p>Another useful tip will be to create a list of products that you need to buy and stick to it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!--Shop smart category block-->
        <!--Store food category block-->
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="avoid-waste-block">
                <div class="food-tip-img" id="store-food">
                    <img src="~/images/store_correctly.png" />
                </div>
                <div id="store-content-block" class="content-block">
                    <p>Keep potatoes, tomatoes, cucumbers, garlic and onions at a room temperature, don’t put them in a refrigerator.</p>
                    <p class="avoid-foodwaste-tip">Try to avoid storing following products together with other fruits or vegetables:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Bananas</li>
                        <li>Avocados</li>
                        <li>Tomatoes</li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Peaches</li>
                        <li>Pears</li>
                        <li>Green Onions</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!--Store food category block-->
        <!--Store food leftover block-->
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="avoid-waste-block">
                <div class="food-tip-img" id="food-leftover">
                    <img src="~/images/save_leftovers.png" />
                </div>
                <div id="leftover-content-block" class="content-block">
                    <p>If you have cooked too much food, don’t throw it away. Put it in a glass container and store in the fridge to have it later.</p>
                    <p>Such an action will help you to avoid food waste, save you time on cooking and money.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!--Store food leftover block-->
        <!--Pack lunch block-->
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="avoid-waste-block">
                <div class="food-tip-img" id="pack-lunch">
                    <img src="~/images/pack_lunch.png" />
                </div>
                <div id="lunch-content-block" class="content-block">
                    <p>Instead of going to a cafe or restaurant for a lunch break, try taking your lunches from home. </p>
                    <p>Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!--Pack lunch block-->
        <!--Egg yolk block-->
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="avoid-waste-block">
                <div class="food-tip-img" id="egg-yolk">
                    <img src="~/images/eat_the_yolk.png" />
                </div>
                <div id="egg-content-block" class="content-block">
                    <p>Unlike popular opinion, studies show that eggs’ yolk does not actually have that much of an impact on cholesterol level, unless you are eating eggs every day for every meal.</p>
                    <p>2-3 eggs with yolk per week will be a healthy decision, since yolk is rich in protein, vitamin A, vitamin B, iron and selenium.</p>
                    <p>If you still don’t want to eat yolk, you can use it as an ingredient in hair and face masks.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!--Egg yolk block-->
        <!--Preserve food block-->
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="avoid-waste-block">
                <div class="food-tip-img" id="preserve-food">
                    <img src="~/images/learn_preserve.png" />
                </div>
                <div id="preserve-content-block" class="content-block">
                    <p>Learn how to preserve food. Pickle, dry, can or freeze it. For example, if your bananas are ripening, cut them and freeze to use later on in smoothies.</p>
                    <p>Bake apple slices in an oven and create a healthy snack for every day.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!--Preserve food block-->
    </div>
</div>


